headlines.description: — Kawhi Leonard couldn't have drawn up a better return.
headlines.shortLinkText: Leonard returns, hits game-winner as Clippers beat Hornets

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Atlanta Hawks

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander scored 35 points, Josh Giddey had 12 of his 17 points in the final period, and the Oklahoma City Thunder overcame a 14-point deficit in the third quarter to beat the Atlanta Hawks 121-114 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander scores 35 as Thunder rally past Hawks

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum had 31 points and 12 rebounds, Jaylen Brown scored 22 points and the Boston Celtics won for the seventh time in eight games, beating the Toronto Raptors 116-110 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum has 31, Celtics beat Raptors 116-110 for 7th win in 8

headlines.description: — Jalen Green scored 27 points and Kevin Porter Jr. added 24 to lead the Houston Rockets to a 132-123 double-overtime victory over the Philadelphia 76ers on Monday night as James Harden struggled through his return from injury.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rockets outlast 76ers in 2 OTs; Harden 4 for 19 in return

headlines.description: — Tyus Jones had a career-high 28 points and 10 assists to lead the short-handed Memphis Grizzlies to a 101-93 victory over Miami Heat on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jones' career-high 28 points lead Grizzlies past Heat 101-93

headlines.description: — Luka Doncic and the Dallas Mavericks got the most important victory over Phoenix in Game 7 of the Western Conference semifinals last season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Doncic, Mavericks preserve big lead, roll past Suns 130-111

events.name: Indiana Pacers at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Rookie Andrew Nembhard outshined the Splash Brothers on their home court.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rookie Nembhard has 31, leads Pacers past Warriors, 112-104
